.el .ds Aq '
.TH devin-mcp 1  "mcp " 
.SH NAME
devin\-mcp \- Connect and log in to Model Context Protocol servers
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdevin mcp\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Connect and log in to Model Context Protocol servers
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
devin\-mcp\-add(1)
Add a new MCP server
.TP
devin\-mcp\-list(1)
List all configured MCP servers
.TP
devin\-mcp\-get(1)
Get details for a specific MCP server
.TP
devin\-mcp\-remove(1)
Remove an MCP server
.TP
devin\-mcp\-login(1)
Authenticate with an MCP server via OAuth
.TP
devin\-mcp\-logout(1)
Remove stored OAuth credentials for an MCP server
.TP
devin\-mcp\-enable(1)
Enable a disabled MCP server
.TP
devin\-mcp\-disable(1)
Disable an MCP server without removing it
.TP
devin\-mcp\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
